summary: REQ-1 appears implemented by routing from Log empty-state to Dashboard with a one-time URL search flag that auto-opens the Add Entry dialog and then clears the flag. REQ-2 appears implemented by adding a daily limit progress section on Dashboard using a Progress UI component and over-limit messaging (over-limit visual styling cannot be fully confirmed due to truncation). REQ-3 appears implemented by removing placeholder social links and rendering icons as non-clickable elements in the footer.

hallucinated_features.description: Added a general-purpose URL parameter/sessionStorage utility module not explicitly requested by the BuildRequest.
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest only asked for specific UX changes on Log empty-state navigation, Dashboard progress indicator, and footer link cleanup; it did not request new URL/sessionStorage helper utilities.

hallucinated_features.description: Added outbound attribution link with UTM parameters based on hostname (appIdentifier).
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest did not request adding/altering tracking parameters or modifying the attribution link behavior beyond cleaning up footer dead social links.
